Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: Meet Dominique — Single mother and small business owner Airfox stories from Brazil: Part 2  After spending the day in Rocinha with Airfox user Robson Carlos, a Brazilian mototaxi driver, bartender, and property manager, we ventured further into the sprawling maze of alleys and streets in South America’s largest favela. We moved through the congested roads, mesmerized by the constant buzz of motorcycles and pedestrians. Nearly a quarter of Rio’s population, or about 1.5 million people, live in the city’s 700+ favelas. These areas, in their irregular and unregulated nature, often lack basic services and public investment. Disparity throughout the city is both profound and highly visible, and a third of the population do not have bank accounts due to exorbitant fees, interest rates, and overly bureaucratic systems. https://medium.com/@Airfox/meet-dominique-single-mother-and-small-business-owner-bfece669a88

My preferred choice for cold-storage is the Ledger Nano S, as it stores the private keys on a special chip that never interacts with your computer, and is considered unhackable because in order to “sign” transactions, the physical buttons on your Ledger must be pushed by hand. One of the benefits of the Ethereum network is that you can store all of your Ethereum tokens (ERC20) on the same Ethereum address. Author: fishervwb
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: Airfox Launches Mobile App in Brazil, Giving Unbanked Citizens Access to Previously Inaccessible Financial Services  Airfox’s free Android app provides millions of unbanked and underbanked Brazilians with access to microloans, mobile payments, and more.  BOSTON & SAO PAULO — Feb. 26, 2018 — Airfox, a mobile financial services company, today launched its free Android app in Brazil, giving millions of people unprecedented access to much-needed financing solutions.  More than 44 percent of Brazil’s population is unbanked, another 30–44 percent lack sufficient access to mainstream financial services, and those with credit cards face interest rates upwards of 200 percent (sources: World Bank, Bloomberg). This financial situation makes it difficult for the majority of Brazilians to rise into the middle class.  Starting today, the millions of people in Brazil with smartphones can skip the bank and instead use the Airfox app to make purchases and apply for and receive microloans. Setting up an Airfox account takes just a few minutes and most users receive a decision on their loan application within days. Brazilians can easily deposit cash into the Airfox app via Boleto Bancário at more than 40,000 locations countrywide. Later this year, Airfox will roll out additional features enabling users to recharge their public transit cards within the Airfox app, pay utility bills, and more. Thanks to a partnership between Airfox and Pareteum (NYSE American: TEUM), MVNOs and MVNEs in Pareteum’s network are now able to provide Airfox’s services to hundreds of thousands of subscribers in Brazil.  Victor Santos, co-founder and CEO of Airfox, said: “Traditional banking in Brazil is expensive, elitist, and bureaucratic. The Airfox app grants Brazilians an enormous amount of economic mobility and added control over their finances. As a Brazilian immigrant and the son of entrepreneurs, I know firsthand the impact a loan can have; even just $50 USD could enable someone to make improvements to their home, cover a medical emergency, or start their own business. We are excited to launch the Airfox app in Brazil with the goal of improving the lives of millions of individuals.”  Because Airfox’s platform is built on the blockchain, the company is able to offer affordable rates, reduced transfer fees, and transparent loan terms. In order to apply for a microloan, users simply opt-in to share their mobile profile with Airfox and start building a credit score through daily smartphone usage. It’s easy for borrowers to repay Airfox loans as well; repayments can be made using cash or money transfer. Airfox app users are segmented into low risk or high risk groups, allowing peer-to-peer lenders to sponsor AirTokens through an Ethereum smart-contract in Airfox’s lending platform.  https://medium.com/@AirFox/airfox-launches-mobile-app-in-brazil-giving-unbanked-citizens-access-to-previously-inaccessible-5f24d03dea79

Author: semsyor
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: Airfox Bi-Weekly Update-December 22, 2017  Hello everyone and happy holidays from the Airfox Team!  The last few months of 2017 have been extremely busy around the office as we prepare for the Q1 2018 product launch! All hands are on deck as we work to ensure a successful introduction of our mobile app into the Brazilian market. This past week an Airfox community member asked a great question in our Discord Chat Channel that was worth sharing! They wanted to know why Airfox has set the product launch for Q1 as opposed to a specific day or month. There will be multiple phases of our product release, in the event we have more than one product launch we want to be able to include it in the quarter it was launched.  Annual Business Strategy Update — Our CEO, Victor will aim to address a majority of these questions in our Annual Business Strategy Update. This update will take place over YouTube Live at 3:00pm EST on Friday, January 5th, 2018. Victor will share the company’s performance throughout the prior year and provide a comprehensive strategic plan for the upcoming year. This strategic plan will include a high-level breakdown on how the firm aims to accomplish these goals. As the date approaches, we will post a link to the different Airfox media channels to let everyone know how to join.  Partnerships — The Business Development team is on pace to close partnerships that will enable our Q1 2018 product launch. Below are the different types of partnerships we aim to work with:  Product — These particular partnerships will be on-boarded to provide a more seamless and efficient experience to our app users. We’re committed to constantly expanding the functionality and capabilities of our app and we know that teaming up with the correct product partners will be vital to accomplishing this. Marketing — User acquisition will be an ongoing focus for Airfox. We want to hit the ground running and a great way to do this is to leverage various marketing partnerships located in our target market. This encompasses working with mainstream brands in the local country to promote our products/services. Blockchain — Blockchain technology is an integral part of our product and is a major contributing factor to our competitive advantage. We’ll constantly look to partner with other blockchain companies to expand our service and product capabilities. As we continue to serve the Brazilian market, we will make product and service changes according to what our users want and need. We constantly aim to integrate our product and services into the daily lives of the unbanked and underbanked Brazilians.  https://medium.com/@AirFox/airfox-bi-weekly-update-december-22-2017-6aff38e3c354

Users: Access to mobile data via token-spotting and advertisers. AIR will be used as the ledger of record for the user’s smart-phone data and personal information. Users can redeem AIR for mobile data recharges across prepaid carriers around the world, and eventually physical and digital products, across publishers and advertisers. Author: James_AirFoxOfficial
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: Originally, we were going to have 150 billion tokens in the ICO, so that individual users of the apps earned a lot of tokens for aesthetic purposes. We got enormous pushback from ICO token purchasers and token exchanges who said 150 billion tokens was too many (read https://medium.com/@AirFox/airtoken-whitepaper-updates-and-token-supply-change-f00e403011f1). So we reduced total supply to 1.5 billion.  Users of our application probably won't know they are using cryptocurrency. They see AIR as "points", just some sort of custom currency they can redeem for data. As such, the amount of AIR displayed in the app is 100x the true value, and the prices of data are also 100x.  For example, if 100 MB of data costs 100 AIR, and you had 100 AIR, in the mobile app itself you would have 10,000 AIR, and 100 MB of data would cost 10,000 AIR.  It's kind of confusing, and we didn't want it this way, but for the token exchanges we had to reduce the token supply.  In the app, you can buy 3355 for $1 USD, but that's actually 33.55 AIR for $1 USD because of the 100x change. The reason you get only 33.55 AIR instead of 50 AIR is that we must pay fiat exchange fees. At $10 USD, we eat the fees because the size of the transaction is large enough to justify it.  I hope this makes sense, let me know if something is unclear.

Author: Airtoken Community
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: A couple excerpts from the Whitepaper relevant to this:  Quote We are launching AIR as an Ethereum ERC20-compliant token for a more efficient and decentralized mobile ecosystem across carriers, advertisers, publishers, and users.  1. Users: Access to mobile capital via micro-loans and advertisers. AIR will be used as the ledger of record for the user’s smart-phone data and personal information. Users will receive AIR rewards for opt-in advertising (instead of the ads being an invisible burden on their data) and micro-loans of AIR based on our internal AirFox user “credit-score,” furnished by AirFox for AirFox internal underwriting guidelines only. Users can redeem AIR for mobile data recharges across prepaid carriers around the world, and eventually physical and digital products, across publishers and advertisers.  2. Carriers: AirFox will programmatically buy airtime and data in bulk from carriers. Carriers want to maximize spectrum and data usage from subscribers in order to maximize revenue. AirFox will purchase data at a discount in bulk across carriers. Users will be able to redeem their AIR into their carrier’s pre-paid account to use for other services outside of mobile data. The carrier benefits from these extra micro-transactions that did not exist before as well as bulk data purchases.  3. Advertisers: Advertisers will have higher ROI, fewer intermediaries, better data targeting, less fraud and low-income user access. Advertisers and developers will be able to target and reach the unbanked prepaid subscriber. Advertisers and programmatic networks can also choose to directly sponsor all or a segment of users with AIR for opt-in, attention or engagement.  4. Publishers: Publishers will have higher monetization, new user reach and a better user experience. Publishers can implement our AIR reward, micro-loan and advertising system to enable higher user output. Publishers can offer an in-app purchase, digital products and physical products as a microloan. They can also allow users to one-click buy their services using their AIR balance. Advertising-based publishers can also reward the users with AIR for being active users or by creating an actionable moment within the publisher's application, website, or other software capable of AIR integration.   Quote AirFox intends to the funds raised via the token sale to buy data in bulk, develop the micro loans program, and expand its consumer-facing business worldwide. AIR will be used across all of our platforms and products. AIR will first be contained to the Browser and Recharge apps, eventually we expect to open up the token to external publishers and advertisers in order to directly enable mobile capital access in their own properties using AIR. AIR will be a utility for mobile data, and eventually it should be further used as we roll-out micro-loans and allow external AIR developers and advertisers to launch our advertising reward and microloan system within their apps and properties.  A couple of suggested resources to check out:  https://www.airtoken.com/paper/AirFoxICO_WhitePaper_v3.0.pdf https://www.airtoken.com/paper/MicroLoan_whitepaper_v1.pdf https://www.airtoken.com/press/index.html https://www.airtoken.com/ - F.A.Q. at the bottom of the page.

Author: Airtoken Community
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: This is an existing company that has already had a lot of success. This is the evolution of that. Here are just a couple small tidbits from the FAQ on the website to digest, with supporting information from the whitepaper:  Why did you start this company? Can you tell me about AirFox? AirFox was founded to provide mobile affordability to the underserved, low-income consumer who is restrained by the cost of data and can’t fully enjoy the benefits of the smartphone. Sara and Victor met while working at Google and saw first hand the power of free search. AirFox wants to take the concept of free search and apply it to mobile data. Quote AirFox’s vision is to make the mobile internet more affordable and accessible and the biggest limitation for our customers is access to capital. AirFox is positioned to create mobile capital for advertisers, users, and carriers using the blockchain. AirFox uses advertising and micro-loans on the blockchain to unlock unrealized mobile capital through a new cryptocurrency - The AirToken.  ___  What is an AirToken? AirToken is the token for mobile access. AIR is a cryptocurrency created by AirFox to enable a more decentralized and efficient mobile ecosystem between carriers, advertisers and publishers to unlock the ‘dead mobile capital’ of data-starved and unbanked or underbanked customers in emerging markets. Through AirTokens, users can recharge their prepaid mobile data plans through direct purchases, earning via advertising, and claiming micro-loans. Quote Over the last year, AirFox’s business-to-business platform has enabled more than 2 million unique U.S. prepaid wireless subscribers to reduce their mobile costs while helping wireless carriers better serve their customers  ___  Find much more info here:  http://www.airtoken.com/index.html http://www.airtoken.com/paper/AirFoxICO_WhitePaper_v1.5.pdf

Author: James_AirFoxOfficial
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: I won't say negative things about DENT, they have an interesting project, but if you read our white paper you will understand that we are fundamentally very different from DENT. DENT plans to integrate with carriers directly to let people exchange unused data for DENT tokens, so they can buy / sell data at lower prices agnostically between carriers. The DENT strategy requires telecom integration into the Ethereum blockchain and telecom buy-in for the DENT token. By pressuring a carrier to support DENT at the risk of losing customers, the hope is that DENT can force the carrier into supporting their technology. This is an adversarial model with the telecom industry. AirFox has an entirely different mission, project, business model, and strategy.  At AirFox, we have worked directly with numerous carriers, understand their technical limitations, and have already built a successful US-focused telecom business. Our technology provides mobile subscribers free data in exchange for opting into ads and completing offers. We have directly integrated with carriers, which is a difficult and long process.  The AirToken strategy is using and extending our software, which we have proven is effective for over 2 million unique users, and expanding globally. We already have connections with over 500 global carriers as part of a data transfer network that we can leverage without needing any carrier buy-in to the Ethereum blockchain or the AirToken.  The AirToken project is about releasing so-called "dead" capital in emerging markets and rewarding users who have very limited access to capital. Users can opt-in to ads, complete offers, and browse the internet using our AirFox Browser app to earn AirTokens. Our software collects personal information allowed by the user (nothing is shared without approval), which includes location data, internet use, their home address, etc. which is extremely difficult to get accurately in these countries. We allow companies to purchase this data directly from users, rewarding them in AirTokens, and also use this information to qualify them for micro-loans, which can be funded in a decentralized platform by any holders of AirTokens to earn interest. With our Android apps, AirFox will be able to give "credit scores" to users based on their risk.  Eventually, the goal is to allow the AirToken platform to exist entirely on the blockchain without AirFox supporting it, giving rise to a truly decentralized market, allowing the AirToken to stay valuable in perpetuity.

Body: A couple tidbits from the FAQ on the website here: http://www.airtoken.com/  What is an AirToken? AirToken is the token for mobile access. AIR is a cryptocurrency created by AirFox to enable a more decentralized and efficient mobile ecosystem between carriers, advertisers and publishers to unlock the ‘dead mobile capital’ of data-starved and unbanked or underbanked customers in emerging markets. Through AirTokens, users can recharge their prepaid mobile data plans through direct purchases, earning via advertising, and claiming micro-loans.  What do AirTokens represent? AirToken is an AirFox product. AirTokens are access to mobile capital in emerging markets, first for the internet than eventually other products and services. When consumers purchase or earn an AirToken they are essentially buying into our vision and buying utility for their own use, either for themselves or for others. The tokens provide real utility enabling anyone to recharge over 5B prepaid sim cards across the world. AirTokens are a utility profuct and are not securities or investment instruments. They are not intended for speculation.

Author: James_AirFoxOfficial
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: I recommend reading the white paper, but the utility functions of the AirToken are redeeming it for mobile data, digital services, physical goods, and provide loans (earning interest) to qualified users. If you are a user of our Android apps, you can earn AirTokens for using opting into ads, completing offers, and using our web browser. Companies can also purchase accurate information directly from users, such as their location and internet data, which is normally very difficult to get in these emerging markets. Providing accurate marketing data for users that are not part of any formal system is quite valuable.  The goal of the AirToken is to allow users to monetize their cell phone, unlocking capital in developing markets. We have successfully accomplished this for low-income users in the USA, and are now expanding globally via the AirToken and the Ethereum blockchain.

Author: Airtoken Community
Title: [ANN][ICO] AirToken | Mobile Data Accessibility | Token Sale Complete $15M USD
Body: Without listing specific carriers as yet, there is some info in the FAQ that pertains here.  What are the benefits for wireless carriers?  Carriers are incentivized to maximize revenue per user since they have high fixed costs.  80% of the world is prepaid but prepaid users have 1/8th of the ARPU of post-paid users with often 3X the churn. In addition, Only 30% of carriers’ spectrum capacity is used so wireless carries benefit from working with AirFox by enabling us to buy data in bulk and monetize these low ARPU subscribers and get them to use more data.  Pre-paid MVNOs like Cricket Wireless and Boost are already established business model examples that serve a niche and a purpose for the underlying Tier-1 Carrier.
